Linear extension
A total order T is a linear extension of a partial order P if , whenever x ≤ y in P it also holds that x ≤ y in T .
Every partial order can be extended to a total order -LRB- order-extension principle -RRB- .
In computer science , algorithms for finding linear extensions of partial orders are called topological sorting .
