Every poset -LRB- and every preorder -RRB- may be considered as a category in which every hom-set has at most one element .
More explicitly , let hom -LRB- x , y -RRB- = -LCB- -LRB- x , y -RRB- -RCB- if x ≤ y -LRB- and otherwise the empty set -RRB- and -LRB- y , z -RRB- o -LRB- x , y -RRB- = -LRB- x , z -RRB- .
Posets are equivalent to one another if and only if they are isomorphic .
In a poset , the smallest element , if any , is an initial object , and the largest element , if any , a terminal object .
Also , every preordered set is equivalent to a poset .
